solutions.content:
A brief about logical approach:
* We have two poiters,
	* `i` at index 0 (for even indices)
	* `j` at index 1 (for odd indices)
* Now we check whether `i` has an `even` number,
	* if `nums[i]` is even : `i+=2` (move to next even index)
	* if `nums[i]` is odd: we check whether `j` has an `odd` number,
		* if `nums[j]` is odd : `j+=2` (move to next odd index)
		* if `nums[j]` is even: swap `nums[i]` and `nums[j]`

Thats it!

If you found it helpful upvote. And if you have any doubts or suggestions, comment them down. ✌


