solutions.content:
# **Explanation**
Copy `arr` into `A` and sort it.
Iterate sorted array `A` and record the rank for each element in hashmap `rank`.
Iterate `arr` again, and assign `rank[arr[i]]` to `A[i]`.
return the final result `A`.
<br>

# **Complexity**
Time `O(NlogN)`
Space `O(N)`
<br>

**Java**
Suggested by @hiepit and @saftageorge 
```java
   public int[] arrayRankTransform(int[] arr) {
        int[] A = Arrays.copyOf(arr, arr.length);
        Arrays.sort(A);
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> rank = new HashMap<>();
        for (int x : A)
          rank.putIfAbsent(x, rank.size() + 1);
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; ++i)
          A[i] = rank.get(arr[i]);
        return A;
    }
```
**C++**
```cpp
    vector<int> arrayRankTransform(vector<int>& arr) {
        vector<int> A(arr);
        sort(A.begin(), A.end());
        unordered_map<int, int> rank;
        for (int& a : A)
            rank.emplace(a, rank.size() + 1);
        for (int i = 0; i < A.size(); ++i)
            A[i] = rank[arr[i]];
        return A;
    }
```
