solutions.content:
Given an array of integers our task is to assign rank to each integer based on size.

Smaller than number, smaller the rank  
larger the number, larger the rank
If two numbers are same their rank should also be same.
Rank starts from 1.
Eg: [4, 7, 3, 8]
o/p: [2, 3, 1, 4]

Idea is to use map so that elements will be in the sorted order and it is easier to assign ranks that way.

```
vector<int> arrayRankTransform(vector<int>& arr)
    {
        map<int,int>mp;
        for(auto x:arr) //push every elements of the array into the map
            mp[x]++;

        int rank=1;
        for(auto x:mp)
        {
            mp[x.first]=rank; //assign rank 1,2 and so on
            rank++;
        }

        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++) //Now copy back the ranks to the array
            arr[i]=mp[arr[i]];
        return arr;
    }
```
T.C-> O(N*LOGN) , Since in maps the sorting factor is involved in the background
S.C-> O(N)

