Aug. 31, 2021
**Introduction**
I decided to subscribe Leetcode premium, so that I can quickly warmup some algorithms to prepare for online assessment. 

**Ranking**
It is interesting to apply ranking in a given array, the idea is to put all elements in the array into a hashset, so that only unique values are stored, and then convert to a C# SortedSet, and then convert to a List, and then save a hashmap to find the index by looking up element value. 

```
public class Solution {
    public int[] ArrayRankTransform(int[] arr) {
        if(arr == null)
        {
            return arr;
        }

        var set = new HashSet<int>(arr);
        var sorted = new SortedSet<int>(set);

        var list = sorted.ToList();
        var map = new Dictionary<int, int>();

        for(int i = 0; i < list.Count; i++)
        {
            map.Add(list[i], i);
        }

        var result = new int[arr.Length];

        for(int i = 0; i < arr.Length; i++)
        {
            result[i] = map[arr[i]] + 1;
        }

        return result; 
    }
}
```

