Feb. 18, 2021
The idea is simple. First put all numbers in the array to a hashset, so all distinct values are saved. Next convert the hashset to a list, sort them in ascending order. Save all values and the order in a C# hashmap. Last, it is easy to figure out each number's ranking based on C# hashmap. 

```
public class Solution {
    public int[] ArrayRankTransform(int[] arr) {
        if(arr == null || arr.Length == 0)
            return new int[0];

        var set = new HashSet<int>(arr);

        var list = set.ToList(); 
        list.Sort(); 
        var map = new Dictionary<int, int>(); 

        for(int i = 0; i < list.Count; i++)
        {
            map.Add(list[i], i + 1); 
        }

        var length = arr.Length; 
        var smallest = new int[length];
        for(int i = 0; i < length; i++)
        {
            smallest[i] = map[arr[i]];
        }

        return smallest; 
    }
}
```

