(2 ^ 3) - encoded[0] ^ encoded[1] ^ encoded[2] ^ encoded[3]

Now, If we XOR (2 ^ 4) (2 ^ 1) (2 ^ 5) (2 ^ 3) together we get (1 ^ 3 ^ 4 ^ 5), now we XOR elements from (1 - 5) [as this is the given range of elements] 

(1 ^ 3 ^ 4 ^ 5) ^ (1 ^ 3 ^ 4 ^ 5 ^ 2) = 2 (First Number)

We can easily generate the array using first number 2.



