# Intuition
It's all about observations

1/  p1 ^ p2 = e1
    p2 ^ p3 = e2
    e1 ^ e2 = p1^p3
    that way we can get all p1 ^ pi for i in [2, n]
    p1^p2 = e1
    p1^p3 = e1^e2
    p1^p4 = e1^e2^e3
    ....
    p1^pn = XOR of all elements (equation 1)

2/  we also know that the elements of perm are from 1 to n
    so we know p1^p2...^pn = 1^2^3...^n (equation 2)

3/  n is **odd**, so in (equation 1), the number of lines is even, so if we do ^ of all the lines, p1^p1 will be done even times and reduced to 0, and now 
    p2^p3^...^pn is know (equation 1)

4/ p1 = (1)^(2)
5/ get all pi from encodes

