        for(int i = 0;i < encoded.size();i++)
            xor_all2 ^= encoded[i];
        int first = xor_all2 ^ last;
        ans[0] = first;
        for(int i = 0;i < encoded.size() - 1;i++){
            ans[i + 1] = encoded[i] ^ ans[i];
        }
        ans[encoded.size()] = last;
        return ans;
    }
};
```
1. **Calculate XOR of perm array i.e 1^2^3...n-1^n -> a**
2. **Calculate XOR of every even indexed(starting from 0) element of encoded array -> b**
3. **Last element = a^b**
4. **Calculate XOR of all elements of encoded array -> c**
5. **First element = c^last_element**.
6. **perm[i + 1] = encoded[i] ^ perm[i] (for i from 0 to encoded.length - 1)**.

