solutions.content:
say orignal array is a1, a2, a3, ...  an
(a1,a2,...,an is a permutation of the set of numbers {1,2,3...,N})

I will try to find out the ith bit of all the numbers.

now the ith bit of a1 can either be 0 or 1.
i make a guess that the ith bit of a1 is 0. 

Since I already know the ith bit of a1^a2 so the ith bit of a2 is fixed which means that the ith bit of a3 is fixed(a2^a3 is known) which means the ith bit of a4 is fixed and so on.

by fixing the ith bit of a1 to 0, the ith bits of all the numbers are known.

Now there are two possibilites 
1) my prediction was wrong and infact the ith bit of a1 is not 0 but 1.
2) my prediction was correct and I can similarly find remaining bits of all numbers.

let Si0 = count of numbers which have their ith bit as 1 when we fix the ith bit of a1 = 0.
let Si1 = count of numbers which have their ith bit as 1 when we fix the ith bit of a1 = 1.
let Ci = count of numbers which have their ith bit as 1 in the set {1,2,3,...,N} 

Claim: our prediction is correct if Si0 equal to Ci else our prediction is wrong and the ith bit of a1 is 1(in which case Si1 equal to Ci) and not 0.

Now you may ask what if Si0 = Si1 = Ci?
Claim: this is not possible.

why is this not possible?
because N(the number of elements is odd). 
okay, so?

so fix ith bit of a1 = 0, then you get x = Si0 numbers with ith bit as 1 and y = (N - Si0) numbers with ith bit as 0.

if you flip the ith bit of a1 from 0 to 1, the ith bits of all numbers will flip(why?) and you will get x = (N - Si0) numbers with ith bit as 0 and Si0 numbers with ith bit as 1.

N - Si0 can never be equal to Si0 because if it is then 2 * Si0 = N meaning that N is even which is not correct as per question.

Hence proved that Si0 = Si1 is not a possibility.

```
class Solution {
public:

int actualNumOf1s(int bit, int N){
      int cnt = 0;
      for(int i = 1; i <= N; i++){
          if((i & (1 << bit)) != 0)
              cnt++;
      }
      return cnt;
}

void setIthBit(int bit, std::vector<int>& nums, std::vector<int>& encoded){
      bool predict = 0; 
      int numOf1s = 0;
      for(int i = 1; i <= encoded.size(); i++){
          bool encodedBit = ((encoded[i - 1] & (1 << bit)) == 0) ? 0 : 1;
          bool thisBit = (predict ^ encodedBit);
          if(thisBit)
            numOf1s++;
          predict = thisBit;
      }
      predict = 0;
      if(numOf1s != actualNumOf1s(bit, nums.size()))
        predict = 1;

      nums[0] += (predict * (1 << bit));
      for(int i = 1; i <= encoded.size(); i++){
          bool encodedBit = ((encoded[i - 1] & (1 << bit)) == 0) ? 0 : 1;
          bool thisBit = (predict ^ encodedBit);
          predict = thisBit;
          nums[i] += (predict * (1 << bit));
      }
}
    vector<int> decode(vector<int>& encoded) {
        cout << actualNumOf1s(0, 3);
        vector<int> answer(encoded.size() + 1);
        for(int bit = 0; bit <= 30; bit++){
            setIthBit(bit, answer, encoded);
        }
        return answer;
    }
};
```

