We can use properties of XOR here. If we XOR alternate elements of the input array and XOR it with total from `1 to n`, we will get the first and the last elements. And then the rest of the process makes use of the following equation

`a^(a^b) == b`

```
class Solution {
    public int[] decode(int[] encoded) {
        int n = encoded.length;
        int res[] = new int[n+1];
        int totalXor = getTotalXor(n+1);
        int alternateOne = getAlternateXor(encoded, 0);
        int alternateTwo = getAlternateXor(encoded, 1);
        res[n] = totalXor ^ alternateOne;
        res[0] = totalXor ^ alternateTwo;
        for(int i = 1; i<n; i++) {
            res[i] = encoded[i-1] ^ res[i-1];
        }

        return res;
    }

    int getAlternateXor(int encoded[], int start) {
        int res = 0;
        for(int i = start; i<encoded.length; i+=2)
            res ^= encoded[i];

        return res;
    }

    int getTotalXor(int n) {
        int res = 0;
        for(int i = 1; i<=n; i++)
            res ^= i;

        return res;
    } 
}
```

