Rest stuff is very easy!
Suppose our answer array is consisting of 5 numbers  then assume XOR of 1 to 5 =A
Now this 1 to 5 are in some order which is not known to us, so suppose they are x1.x2.x3.x4.x5 ans we have to find x1 out of this.
So, x1^x2=e1
x2^x3=e2
x3^x4=e3
x4^x5=e4
Here e is given array
so x2^x3^x4^x5=e2^e4
x1^e2^e4=A;
So x1=A^e2^e4;


